# Copy to /etc/django-admin-automation.env (or export before run_production.sh).
# FLASK_DEBUG=0
# BIND=0.0.0.0:5000
# GUNICORN_THREADS=64
# GUNICORN_TIMEOUT=0
# PIPELINE_WORKERS=5
# FLASK_SECRET_KEY=change-me-long-random-string
# DJANGO_TARGET_ENV=beta
# SECRETS_DECRYPTION_KEY is optional here if you use ./run_production.sh (sources .secrets.env, secrets.local.env, then .secrets.key)
# or rely on server.py auto-loading those files on import. Set below only if you use raw gunicorn without those files:
# SECRETS_DECRYPTION_KEY=your-secrets-enc-passphrase
# BETA_JUPYTER_* / PROD_JUPYTER_* are not required on this service — Jupyter helper/base64 scripts are run separately, not by Gunicorn.
# If admin 404s for evaluation metrics, set the changelist path after /admin/:
# Beta uses typo "evalution" in the URL segment:
# DJANGO_EVAL_METRICS_MODEL_PATH=nkb_question/codingquestiontestcaseevalutionmetrics/
# Optional extra paths to try (comma-separated):
# DJANGO_EVAL_METRICS_MODEL_PATH_ALTERNATES=nkb_question/coding_question_test_case_evaluation_metric/
# Optional: require Bearer token on POST /api/* (breaks browser UI unless a proxy injects the header).
# AUTOMATION_API_TOKEN=
